flowRoot.flowPara: Insert your prepared slide here (be careful slotting it in not to push your coverslip away)
Inject equal amounts (0.5ml) of silicon from syringe A and fixer from syringe B and mix well
Place your chip logo surface down into the mix, pressing gently to the bottom of the dish. Cover and leave to set for 3 hours (spin if you have a dremelfuge)
Carefully remove from the mix then with a scalpel and tweezers remove the recessed impression of the chip and carefully place on your microscope slide, impression down

Use the micro disposable pipette to inject a drop of algae suspenstion into the side of the impressed silicon. Capilliary action should pull the liquid into the tiny impressions of the chip surface markings or the vinyl channels
